    CaughtValue

    CustomVar
    Visit custom variable with a name It will be created when it doesn't exist To interact between injectors Be careful not to use overly simplistic name
    LocalVar
    To visit a local variable(include arg) You can change the variable if receive a WrappedObject Otherwise,get the variable only
    ManualByteCode
    Generate bytecode injected manually Injection must be a static method: 1st arg is a NothingMethod meaning the injected method 2nd arg is a List<AbstractInsnNode> meaning the bytecodes of the method before being injected 3rd arg is a AbstractInsnNode meaning location of injection, codes should be injected before it Return void
    NothingByteCode  
    NothingInject
    Sign an injecting The injecting should return Optional<T>, where T is return value of the method injected Returning null means to continue running Returning Optional.ofNullable(v) means forces the target method to return v or v.getRaw()
    NothingInjects  
    StackTop
    Take out value at current stack top, then put it back later You can receive WrappedObject to change it
